article.headline: Wecker leads Wildcats with 20 points, 14 boards
article.linkText: No. 17 K-State hands Colorado 9th straight loss
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- Kendra Wecker had 20 points and 14 rebounds to lead Kansas State (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) to a 73-51 victory over Colorado on Saturday night.

Wecker broke former teammate Nicole Ohlde's career rebounding mark, finishing the game with a school-record 1,002 for the Wildcats (18-6, 9-4 Big 12).

Laurie Koehn finished with 15 points, hitting five 3-pointers to move into third place on the NCAA 3-point list, and Megan Mahoney added 14 points and four assists to break Mary Jo Miller's school career assists record. Mahoney has 565 assists.

Veronica Johns-Richardson led Colorado (8-16, 1-12) with 14 points, and Jasmina Ilic and Kara Richards added 10 points each. Colorado matched the longest losing streak in school history with its ninth loss in a row.

Wecker scored Kansas State's first nine points and then combined with Koehn to give the Wildcats a 17-9 lead. Twiggy McIntyre added a basket and Shana Wheeler hit a free throw before Mahoney got in on the act, rattling off five straight points to make it 25-16.

The Buffaloes didn't have a field goal for the final 10:08 of the first half, and Jessica McFarland's scooping layup gave Kansas State a 38-23 halftime lead.

The Wildcats scored the first six points of the second half for a 44-26 lead.

The Buffaloes shot just 33 percent from the field and were 5-for-19 from 3-point range, going nearly 15 minutes without a field goal midway through the game.
